Edward H. MOORE v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE. No. 633. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Feb. 23, 1932. L. Karlton Mostellor, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. C. M. Charest, Gen. Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for respondent.

*1070Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Petition for review dismissed on motion of petitioner.
